@Technicaldev: Thanks for the report. This issue was actually reported elsewhere in <a class="closed ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/33442" title="#33442: defect (bug): Widgets not displayed if no $instance data is set (closed: fixed)">#33442</a>. The issue will be “fixed” in 4.3.1, however as you can read in the comments on the ticket, I would argue that the plugin is doing the wrong thing by returning <code>null</code> from the <code>WP_Widget::update()</code> method. WordPress is expecting this method to be returning an array, even an empty one. So for the immediate fix, I recommend updating the plugin to return an array instead of null. Thanks!
